search - Git Repository Search

USAGE:
    search [options] <search-term>

DESCRIPTION:
    Search within git repositories. Can search contents, filenames,
    logs, branches, and tags across projects and branches.

OPTIONS:
    -a
        Search all projects AND branches

    -r
        Search all projects in current directory

    -l
        List matched files only

    -x=CMD
        Execute CMD for each found file

    -C
        Search project contents only (no filenames or logs)

    -F
        Search project filenames only (no logs or contents)

    -L
        Search project logs only (no filenames or contents)

    -A
        Search activity only (/activity/)

    -s=YYYY/MM/DD
        Start date for log searches

    -e=YYYY/MM/DD
        End date for log searches

    -contents (default)
        Search content with options:
        -xedit      Use $conf_search_xeditor
        -edit       Use $conf_search_editor
        -files      Use $conf_search_file_manager

        -commits=current    Search current working tree (default)
        -commits=any        Search across all commits in current branch
        -commits=all        Search across current HEAD of each branch

    -changes
        Search changes with options:
        -branches       Search in specified branch
        -all-branches   Search in all branches
        -i             Case insensitive

    -logs
        Search logs with options:
        -branches       Search in specified branch
        -all-branches   Search in all branches
        -i             Case insensitive

    -branches
        Search branch names

    -tags
        Search tag names

    -type=git/branches
    -type=git/changes
    -type=git/logs
    -type=system
    -type=git/tags

ARGUMENTS:
    search-term
        Term to search for (required)

CONFIGURATION:
    -conf-search-xeditor CMD
        External editor for search results

    -conf-search-editor CMD
        Editor for search results

    -conf-search-file-manager CMD
        File manager for search results

EXAMPLES:
    search "function name"
    search -l "import java"
    search -a -r "TODO"
    search -logs -branches=main "fix bug"
    search -type=git/branches "feature"
